pageContext.claim: “I watch Judge Kavanaugh, who is central casting, a great intellect, top student at Yale.”
pageContext.analysis: Kavanaugh went to Yale for his undergraduate degree and Yale Law School. As an undergraduate, he graduated cum laude, which follows summa cum laude and magna cum laude as rankings for academic excellence. No more than five percent of seniors graduate summa cum laude, the next ten percent magna cum laude and the following fifteen percent cum laude.
